-- Australian Unions Should Keep Right to Prosecute on Safety, Premier Says
-- B y   M a r i o n   R a e
-- 2010-10-18T00:00:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/nsw-state-unions-should-keep-right-to-prosecute-on-safety-premier-says.html
Australia’s state of New South Wales
wants an exemption for unions to have the right to prosecute
over workplace safety, Premier Kristina Keneally told reporters
in Sydney today.  Prime Minister Julia Gillard’s threat of financial
penalties if the state retains different laws is “heavy
handed” and “premature,” Keneally added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marion Rae in Canberra at 
